A police officer on Tuesday shot and seriously injured two people before killing himself at Litein Diamond bar, in Bureti sub-county. The officer who recently graduated from Embakasi AP College had been assigned duty IEBC offices at Litein. Kericho county commissioner Muktar Abdi said the officer got angry after a bar attendant refused to serve him alcohol because he was armed and on duty. This is when he opened fire and shot the bar attendant on the stomach and another reveller who was having a drink the club. The injured were rushed to Litein Mission Hospital in Bureti sub-county for treatment. The body of the late is at Kapkatet AIC Mission Hospital in Bureti sub-county. Abdi said the officer was armed with an AK 47 rifle. Click here for the latest political news    